Inventory


Making Your Money Work for You






Predictable Disappointment







Show Me the Money!







Size (and Location) Matters







Integrated and Capital Planning







You know it’s going to be bad, but how bad?  Let’s get some perspective here.  One of the things we love about the inventory solution in IBP is the ability to predict service levels.  Yeah it’s a glass half full kind of thing, but wouldn’t you rather know ahead of time rather than scramble at the last minute?  We would, but then again, we’re planners.






 Let’s talk a language that everyone understands; cash.  With IBP inventory optimization you don’t have to focus on abstract measurements  like volume and mass, but can instead focus on dimensions that matter, like dollars and cents.  The ability to project capital requirements to support a given supply plan is a major unlock for S&OP, and business planning.  Impress your wall-street friends with your new vocabulary, courtesy of IBP and SCMC.






Now where did I put that inventory in the first place? Why, the most efficient spot imaginable of course!  With IBP inventory it’s not just the size of your stockpile, but where you put it that counts.  This means the ability to scientifically maintain service levels with the most efficient inventory plan imaginable.  Maybe it’s closer to the customer, maybe it’s in components.  Only IBP inventory knows the sweet spot to maximize your service every single time.






What happens when finance and supply chain work together on a single goal like a harmonized supply plan?  We don’t know, because it’s never happened.  But what if you just stop talking past each other and at least appreciate the other’s viewpoint?  Cordial meetings!  When supply chains can work within capital constraints and sales, finance and marketing can see the physical impact of their plans in cold hard cash.  Now we’re talking.






