Response Planning


 When Planning Becomes Reacting






Dealer's Choice







Prioritize!







Quick Actions







Consistent Policies







When you only have so much love to give, don’t get all emotional about it…  Play by the house rules.  When you pre-determine a set of rules by product, customer or segment the panic room becomes a planning room.  Since you’re not reinventing the wheel each time, whenever things get tight, just play by the rules.  Response in IBP allows consistent and fair execution of those rules.  So crunch-time becomes go-time.






 I know they’re all your favorites, but you’ve got to choose!  When safety stock turns into not enough stock, you need to prioritize.  Rather than make it up on the fly, make a decision.  Prioritize by demand type, customer type, or whatever other type you need to make a decision on.  The IBP response module will peg demand to supply, show the issues and help triage.  In short, IBP response makes order out of chaos.






When reacting to customer expectations requires cat-like reflexes then it helps to have a plan in advance.  Don’t get caught flatfooted.  Jump into action with (mostly) well thought out priorities in IBP response.  How easy is it to setup?  So easy a user can use it.  The simple and easy to follow prioritization logic of IBP response allows users to support users.  React as plans change, and setup the system to follow.






Planners might actually take days off.  Sometimes they even quit or possibly even get promoted.  And then what?  Institutionalize your tribal knowledge with consistent service policies.  It’s time to take instinct out of the gut and put it into ones and zeroes.  Setting up a response plan that matches the goals of a changing organization can get everyone singing the same song, and it’s even better if that song isn’t “The Way We Were.”






