S&OP


The Art of Herding Cats






Everyone in the Pool!







Side by Side







Money Talks







Stop! Collaborate and Listen







We’re all in this together, so let’s grudgingly walk into the same meeting and hash this out.  But what if we’re all working off the same data?  At the same time?  In the same system?  OK now we have your attention.  With IBP S&OP Planning you can work with sales, finance, marketing, supply and execution all looking at the same bit and bytes.  Sure, everyone has their own lens and their own graph, but at least cause and effect is shown across all groups.  Now we can all disagree on the same dataset.  Progress!






What if unicorns were real?  What if I could hold my breath for 15 minutes?  Ever wondered what if?  So do we, and with IBP you can see what those what-if’s look like in real life.  With side by side fully integrated planning, every scenario you think of can be analyzed from the perspective of the demand, supply or inventory planner.  Then the impact of those plans can be compared side by side in a virtual cage match.  Look at the impact of your decisions across the entire supply chain quickly, easily, and seamlessly with IBP.






We’re studying our Esperanto every single night.  But until that catches on, money is the universal language of business.  So we speak dollars and cents.  That means the bottom line in Every. Single. Decision. So go ahead, look at the profitability of your hunch, view the overhead of your strategy.  We’ll wait, it will all come out in the wash, and we’ll pick the obvious answer that saves us the most money (its usually option C).  Trust us… we’re executives in training.






Team work makes dreams work.  That’s our motto.  And with IBP S&OP functionality it becomes a reality.  Sharing a single database in a unified planning area allows for all teams, from demand, to supply to finance and yes, even marketing to collapse on problems like never before.  New product introductions?  Glad to meet you!  Annual planning?  Seems like only yesterday!  With IBP you can collaborate with a whole new attitude, and present your (best) plan forward.  Go Team!






